Durban - A horror crash on the N2 near Joyner Road claimed the lives of two people a short while ago. According to Garrith Jamieson of Rescue Care Paramedics a truck and a delivery vehicle collided before both vehicles veered off the road. "A male and female were killed," said Jamieson. He said when paramedics arrived on scene to find carnage. "Paramedics assessed the scene and found that the two occupants of the bakkie a male and a female believed to be in their forties had sustained major injuries and there was nothing more paramedics could do for them and they were declared deceased on the scene. "The truck driver had sustained moderate injuries and were stabilised on the scene before being transported to a nearby Hospital for the further care that he required. At this stage the events leading up to the collision is unknown however SAPS were on the scene and will be investigating further added Jamieson. POST 